The paper discusses the emergence of spatial knowledge in autonomous agents through sensorimotor prediction, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to capture spatial invariants, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of exploratory conditions to facilitate the emergence of spatial representations, which suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
